Method Detail

isShared

public boolean isShared()
Checks whether IP finder is shared or not.

If it is shared then only coordinator can unregister addresses.

All nodes should register their address themselves, as early as possible on node start.

Specified by:
isShared in interface GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinder
Returns:
true if IP finder is shared.

setShared

@GridSpiConfiguration(optional=true)
public void setShared(boolean shared)
Sets shared flag. If true then it is expected that IP addresses registered with IP finder will be seen by IP finders on all other nodes.

Parameters:
shared - true if this IP finder is shared.
